cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with properties and algorithms related to polygons in the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of triangulation algorithms suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and the 3SUM-hardness result points to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and complexity theory (cs.CC). The Erd\H{o}s-Szekeres type results suggest a connection to combinatorics (cs.DM) and the concept of generalized geometric permutations suggests a connection to computational geometry and topology (cs.GT).
